  <TITLE>Move back from &quot;short time&quot; caching to &quot;per request&quot; caching</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>There's no any real need to cache many entities between HTTP requests, even for 3 minutes (a default value). For example, customers, mapping between customers and customer roles generic attributes. It doesn't make any sense and just &quot;bloat&quot; the memory. Furthermore, after some testing we've found out that it could reduce usage of CPU and memory. Further performance optimization is related to &quot;long time&quot; caching. There's no need cache in long term entities such as forum posts and topics, forum votes, private messages, queued emails, newsletter subscription. All of them should be cached in &quot;short term&quot; (so now only during the current HTTP request)</DESCRIPTION>
  <REPONAME>nopCommerce</REPONAME>
  <TIMEDIFFERENCEDAYS>22</TIMEDIFFERENCEDAYS>
